					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10621807#post-4609269</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10621807/scp-4727#post-4609269</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 22 Apr 2020 23:46:00 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Elogee FishTruck</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4037075</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I really enjoyed Appendix A. Not even including the funny footnote, the micro-questions that are formed while reading the Appendix (like &quot;why was Inez killed&quot; and &quot;how did Thomas get the gun&quot;) are answered cleanly in the very same Appendix in a way I find very clever. I feel you could go without Appendix B as it stands, as it doesn't really include anything we don't already know and the D-class test isn't adding much of anything, but the rest of the skip is stellar.</p> <p>Now I just want to know what happens when the same user uses it twice. +1.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
